bject containing data that will be passed to the event handler.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li id=\"scroll-eventData-handler-handler\">\n<div><strong>handler<\/strong><\/div>\n<div>Type: <a href=\"http:\/\/api.jquery.com\/Types\/#Function\">Function<\/a>( <a href=\"http:\/\/api.jquery.com\/Types\/#Event\">Event<\/a> eventObject )<\/div>\n<div>A function to execute each time the event is triggered.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li class=\"signature\">\n<h4 class=\"name\">\n<span class=\"version-details\">version added: <a href=\"\/category\/version\/1.0\/\">1.0<\/a><\/span><a id=\"scroll\" href=\"#scroll\"><span class=\"icon-link\"><\/span>.scroll()<\/a>\n<\/h4>\n<ul><li><div class=\"null-signature\">This signature does not accept any arguments.<\/div><\/li><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"longdesc\" id=\"entry-longdesc\">\n    <div class=\"warning\">\n      <p>This API is deprecated.<\/p>\n      <p>Instead of <code>.scroll( handler )<\/code> or <code>.scroll( eventData, handler )<\/code>, use <a href=\"\/scroll\/#on1\"><code>.on( \"scroll\", handler )<\/code><\/a> or <a href=\"\/scroll\/#on1\"><code>.on( \"scroll\", eventData, handler )<\/code><\/a>, respectively.<\/p>\n      <p>Instead of <code>.scroll()<\/code>, use <a href=\"\/scroll\/#trigger2\"><code>.trigger( \"scroll\" )<\/code><\/a>.<\/p>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n<\/div><\/article>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Bind an event handler to the &#8220;scroll&#8221; event, or trigger that event on an element.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[32,22,78,91],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-624","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-browser-events","category-deprecated-33","category-78","category-91"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/api.jquery.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/624","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"c